version_description: This is how I think Pete Murray plays it. You can play the chords noted below, you just have to add two strings to some of them. Those are only the two strings at the B and e at the 3rd fret. Then there is also a chord which doens't have a name (I think), so i'll just name it Switch chord (Sc), because he uses it to switch between the G - Em sequence. The chorus and outro are played with normal chords. I wrote down the chords below in the diagram. Hope you understand it.
This tab is an in-depth guide on how to play the song, it is really accurate. Better than the others.
Combined chords and words together so that you don't have to memorise everything...
